com.davidsoergel.trees

Class AbstractHierarchyNode<KV,H extends HierarchyNode<KV,H>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.davidsoergel.trees.AbstractHierarchyNode<KV,H>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    HierarchyNode<KV,H>, Iterable<H>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractDoubleHierarchicalTypedProperties, AbstractHierarchicalTypedPropertyNode, ListHierarchyNode, SetHierarchyNode

    public abstract class AbstractHierarchyNode<KV,H extends HierarchyNode<KV,H>>
extends Object
implements HierarchyNode<KV,H>
    Abstract implementation of some of the most basic HierarchyNode functionality. Concrete classes extending this need implement only getChildren() and newChild(), because they must choose what kind of Collection to use for the children.
    Version:
    $Id: AbstractHierarchyNode.java 524 2009-10-10 07:55:47Z soergel $
    Author:
    David Soergel

      • depthFirstIterator

        public DepthFirstTreeIterator<KV,H> depthFirstIterator()
        Description copied from interface: HierarchyNode
        Get an iterator that returns all the nodes of the tree in depth-first order. The breadth ordering may or may not be defined, depending on the HierarchyNode implementation. We provide this depth-first iterator explicitly even though the HierarchyNode is itself iterable, because the default iterator may be breadth-first or something else.
        Specified by:
